comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-03T05:05:25.727Z",codex-sdk-explorer,"Explorer finding 2026-06-03: SDK/schema inspection confirms this is the canonical item for schema list/show. Public primitives today: @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk exports defineExtension, ExtensionApi, SchemaItemTypeDefinition/SchemaFieldDefinition/SchemaMigrationDefinition, ExtensionRegistrationRegistry, getContracts/getWorkspaceContracts; extensions can call api.registerItemTypes/registerItemFields/registerMigration with schema capability. Runtime type registry merges built-ins + settings/schema/types.json + extension registerItemTypes, but current pm schema CLI/MCP/contracts expose only add-type. Combined PR should make list/show source-aware (builtin, configured file/settings, extension with layer/name), update CLI/MCP/contracts/completion/docs/tests, and include extension-registered type coverage so package authors can verify activation before create."
  "2026-06-03T05:16:09.435Z",codex-main,"Evidence: Implemented pm schema list/show with compact human output and JSON builtin/custom/extension groups, full show definitions, extension provenance for extension-owned types, CLI/MCP/SDK contracts/completion coverage, and docs. Verification passed: pnpm build; linked pm test --run for schema/contracts/completion/sdk tests; temp dogfood init --type-preset research + schema list/show + create Experiment + health; pnpm quality:docs-skills; pnpm quality:static; pnpm changelog:pm:check using pm-changelog 2026.6.2 unchanged; pm health --check-only --summary ok; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage 2120 tests 100%. pm validate history drift ok; resolution warnings are pre-existing closed-item metadata warnings."
